time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Fusion
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 638 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  protein: 39 g
course: main course
---

First get your veggies prepped! Cut each of the @cherry tomatoes{1} into quarters. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, then peel and chop really finely. Roughly chop the @coriander{3} and zest half the @lime{1/2}.

Put the onion in a #small frying pan{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook on medium-low heat for ~{15%minutes} until it is soft and sweet.

> Tip: Turn the heat lower if necessary so it doesn't end up burning.

In a #bowl{} mix three-quarters of your coriander, the tomatoes and @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{good grind}. Squeeze over @lime juice{1 1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}, mix and leave to the side.

Put @water{300%ml} in a #pot{} with the @chicken stock pot{1/2} and @olive oil{1%tsp}. Once it comes to the boil add in the @couscous{3/4}. Cover the pot with a tightly fitting #lid{}, take it off the heat and leave to the side until the rest of your meal is ready.

Rub @olive oil{1/4%tsp} onto each @salmon fillet{2} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Put the @sesame seeds{3} on a #plate{} or #board{} and roll the salmon in the sesame seeds, coating the fillets on all sides. Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, cook the salmon for ~{4%minutes} on each side turning only once.

Fluff up your couscous with a #fork{}. Add your lime zest, your slow cooked red onion and mix all of this together.

Serve your couscous in #bowls{} with your salmon on top. Spoon over a healthy portion of the tomatoes and a sprinkle of coriander.